overview: The user requested a thorough browser-based testing of the sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent started by verifying the dev server was
  running and then navigated through the application. It tested the main
  questionnaire flow, including filling out sections manually and using a
  "Pre-fill & Jump to Report (Dev)" button to quickly reach the report section.
  The agent successfully tested the PDF report download functionality and
  confirmed the  endpoint was working. It then attempted to
  test the admin dashboard, verifying that the login page was protected and that
  incorrect login attempts triggered appropriate error messages. During testing,
  the agent encountered some UI navigation quirks, such as the page not
  appearing to advance immediately after clicking "Next Section" or "Pre-fill",
  which were attributed to potential React rendering timing issues. Despite
  these minor observations, core functionalities like conditional fields, report
  generation, PDF download, and API responses were confirmed to be working as
  expected.
